                            <comment id="17083945" author="paulk" created="Wed, 15 Apr 2020 09:22:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A workaround would be to use SimpleTemplateEngine or GStringTemplateEngine - though they may not be as performant in some scenarios.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17083963" author="paulk" created="Wed, 15 Apr 2020 09:41:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The issue can illustrated outside templates and seems to be an issue with the grammar. It can be simplified to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;.each { ; x = 0 }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which passes under 2.5.x but fails in 3+ with:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Unexpected input: &apos;{&apos;; Expecting &amp;lt;EOF&amp;gt; at line: 1, column: 11
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It can be fixed by removing the unneeded semicolon. I don&apos;t know whether we could adjust StreamingTemplateEngine to do that but seems worth seeing if the grammar can be tweaked first.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17085887" author="daniel_sun" created="Fri, 17 Apr 2020 15:53:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed by&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/cb05f9acc4696f206e2d804c973edbfc04636c3f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/cb05f9acc4696f206e2d804c973edbfc04636c3f&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
